         <abstract>
            <p>
               Let B and T be n × n real matrices and r and n-vector and consider the system u = BTu + r. A new sufficient condition is given for the existence of a solution and convergence of a monotone process to a solution. The monotone process is a generalization of the Collatz-Schröder procedure. 
            </p>
